          "grocery-bot-gpu/production_run.py",
          "grocery-bot-gpu/fetch_token.py"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "gpu_beam_search.py lines 350-361: torch.compile fallback chain has three nested except Exception: pass blocks -- if compilation fails silently, the user gets no indication that performance may be degraded.",
          "production_run.py:259: subprocess.Popen for DB import wrapped in 'except Exception: pass'. capture_from_game_log.py:269: Popen for DB import in 'except Exception: pass'. fetch_token.py has three bare 'except Exception:' blocks.",
          "While some are intentional best-effort operations, there is no consistent pattern distinguishing critical vs optional error paths."
        ],
        "suggestion": "For best-effort operations (DB import, background tasks), log a debug-level message explaining the silent catch. For the torch.compile chain, emit a warning to stderr when all compile backends fail (e.g., print('Warning: torch.compile unavailable, using uncompiled kernels', file=sys.stderr)). Establish a convention: # BEST-EFFORT comments above intentional silent catches.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "fixed",
      "note": "Fixed bare except blocks to use except Exception, added comments to silent catch handlers explaining why they are intentional, added traceback logging to stderr in critical paths",
