    "review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::inconsistent-logging-mechanism::af2270ea": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::convention_outlier::inconsistent-logging-mechanism::af2270ea",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "low",
      "summary": "Diagnostic output uses print(file=sys.stderr) everywhere instead of Python's logging module, and some files redirect sys.stderr to files",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "convention_outlier",
        "related_files": [
          "grocery-bot-gpu/gpu_beam_search.py",
          "grocery-bot-gpu/gpu_sequential_solver.py",
          "grocery-bot-gpu/_reactive_solve_worker.py",
          "grocery-bot-gpu/live_gpu_stream.py"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "All diagnostic output uses print(..., file=sys.stderr). _reactive_solve_worker.py:28-29 reassigns sys.stderr and sys.stdout to a file object, which would break any code expecting these to be the real streams.",
          "live_gpu_stream.py uses _emit() for JSON SSE events on stdout and print(file=sys.stderr) for diagnostics.",
          "No module uses Python's logging module, meaning there is no way to filter verbosity levels, add timestamps, or route output without modifying source code."
        ],
        "suggestion": "While print-to-stderr is a valid pattern for CLI tools and acceptable in competition code, the _reactive_solve_worker.py sys.stderr reassignment is fragile. At minimum, that worker should use a dedicated file handle rather than replacing the global stderr. For the broader codebase, if log filtering becomes needed, migrating to logging.getLogger(__name__) would be straightforward since all output already flows through print calls.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "fixed",
      "note": "Fixed _reactive_solve_worker.py: replaced sys.stderr/stdout reassignment with dedicated _log_fh file handle, updated all print and traceback calls to use _log_fh, added try/finally for proper cleanup. Rest of codebase intentionally uses print(file=sys.stderr) as consistent pattern for CLI competition code.",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-04T21:11:44+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-04T21:11:44+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-04T21:20:20+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "python",
