      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "live_gpu_stream.py has 21 except-Exception blocks, many of which catch all exceptions and only print to stderr. Background workers (_mapf_worker, _gpu_worker, _per_round_worker) catch Exception broadly and continue, potentially masking bugs like tensor shape mismatches or CUDA OOM errors that should propagate differently than expected solver failures.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "grocery-bot-gpu/live_gpu_stream.py"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "live_gpu_stream.py: 21 'except Exception' occurrences (highest in codebase)",
          "_mapf_worker (line ~246): catches Exception, prints traceback, returns silently",
          "_gpu_worker: catches Exception per pass, logs, continues to next pass \u00e2\u20ac\u201d CUDA OOM treated same as trivial error",
          "SvelteKit iterate/+server.js: 'try { JSON.parse(line) } catch (e) {}' silently swallows parse errors in 10+ locations"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Differentiate between expected failures (solver returning low score, network timeout) and unexpected failures (CUDA OOM, tensor shape error). For the latter, either re-raise or set a flag that prevents further GPU calls. In the SvelteKit pipeline, at minimum log parse errors rather than silently swallowing.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
