      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "low",
      "summary": "Logging to stderr uses inconsistent patterns across the Python codebase. Most GPU solver files use print(msg, file=sys.stderr), but some files use bare print() to stdout for status. The SvelteKit endpoints use sendEvent() for structured logging. Within live_gpu_stream.py alone, logging mixes: print(f'  [label] msg', file=sys.stderr) with self._emit({'type': 'event', ...}) to stdout JSON. The bracket-prefix convention ([mapf], [gpu], [zig], [replay]) is consistent within iterate/+server.js but not used in the Python files.",
